These are the top ten largest hotels in the United States of America (USA), based on the number of hotel rooms. The list includes both single buildings and campuses of a single hotel comprising two or more buildings. Also: Top Ten Largest Malls in the USA Las Vegas, an internationally renowned major resort city known primarily for its gambling, shopping, fine dining, entertainment, and nightlife, alone has 26 hotels with capacities of at least 2,000 rooms and has the top 9 largest hotels in the USA. Here is the list The Venetian & Palazzo is the largest hotel in the USA and number one on our list with over 7,000 rooms including 4,049 rooms and 3,068 suites. It is actually made up of two hotels i.e. the Venetian and the Palazzo, under one roof, Located on the Las Vegas Strip in Paradise, Nevada, on the site of the old Sands Hotel, the Venetian & Palazzo features a 120,000-square-foot casino floor, the 2 million-square-foot Sands Expo Convention Center, 12 pools, and more than 40 restaurants and bars. The hotel was first opened back in May 1999.  Located on the Las Vegas Strip in Paradise, Nevada, the MGM Grand is the largest single hotel in the United States with a total of 6,852 rooms and the second-largest hotel in general in the North American country behind the combined Venetian and Palazzo. It features a total of five outdoor pools, rivers, and waterfalls that cover 6.6 acres (2.7 ha), a 380,000 square feet convention center, the MGM Grand Garden Arena, and the Grand Spa. It also houses numerous shops, nightclubs, restaurants, and the largest casino in Clark County, which occupies 171,500 square feet of area. The MGM Grand opened in 1993.  Also known as CityCenter Las Vegas, the CityCenter complex is a collection of multiple structures developed on 76 acres piece of land, which is the former site of the Boardwalk Hotel and Casino the parking space of the Bellagio, and other commercial structures, on the Las Vegas Strip in Paradise, Nevada. The development features a 4,000-room hotel and casino (Aria); two 400-room boutique hotels (The Residences at Mandarin Oriental with 227 residential condo units, and The Harmon Hotel and Spa); a purely residential offering (Veer Towers); a condo-hotel (Vdara condo-hotel); and a 500,000 sq. ft. (46,000 m2) retail and entertainment district. It has a total of 6,790 rooms, which lands it at number 3 in our list of the largest hotels in the United States of America (USA). The CityCenter complex was opened in 2009.  Comprising the Wynn Las Vegas, often simply referred to as Wynn, and Encore Las Vegas (also called Encore at Wynn Las Vegas; often just called Encore), the Wynn resort complex is a luxury resort and casino located on the Las Vegas Strip in Paradise, Nevada, on the site of the old Desert Inn Hotel. Built on 215 acres piece of land the complex has a total of 4,748 rooms, over 190,000 sq. ft. of casino, over 1 million sq. ft. of convention center 30, 000+ sq. ft. of retail space, spa and salon, restaurants, bars, nightclub, and beach club. Wynn resort complex opened in April 2005.  Mandalay Bay is a 2 block luxury resort and casino complex located on the Las Vegas Strip in Paradise, Nevada. One of the property’s blocks operates as the Delano (formerly known as THEhotel), the other one is occupied by Mandalay Bay and Four Seasons Hotel from the 35th to the 39th. Mandalay Bay has 3,209 hotel rooms, 24 elevators, and a casino of 135,000 square feet. Adjacent to the hotel is the 2-million-square-foot Mandalay Bay Convention Center and the 12,000-seat Michelob Ultra Arena. The 43-story Delano Las Vegas on the other hand has 1,117-rooms. First opened in 1999, the entire Mandalay Bay resort complex has a total of 4,426 rooms.  Luxor Las Vegas is a hotel and casino comprising 30 storey iconic pyramid and twin 22 storey hotel towers, situated on the southern end of the Las Vegas Strip in Paradise, Nevada. The iconic pyramid first opened its doors in 1993 while the twin 22 story hotel towers were added to the property in 1998 allowing it to claim its position as the second biggest hotel in Vegas at the time. With a total of 4,407 rooms, the Luxor Las Vegas is currently the 6th largest hotel in Vegas and the entire United States of America. The hotel has a five-acre pool area with four pools, a whirlpool and 12 private cabanas, and a 120,000-square-foot casino with over 2,000 slot machines and 87 table games.  Located on the Las Vegas Strip in Paradise, Nevada, Excalibur Hotel and Casino is a castle-themed resort and casino that features a 100,000-square-foot gaming area that consists of table games and more than 1,200 slot machines. In addition to casino space, the Excalibur Hotel and Casino includes a renovated pool area, a 13,000-square-foot spa, and fitness center, eight restaurants, and a food court, the Chapel at Excalibur, the Octane Lounge with live music on the weekends, and an arcade. Opened on June 19, 1990, as the largest hotel in the world, with 3,981 rooms covering over 70 acres, the hotel also has 4 outdoor pools featuring a water slide, poolside cabanas, and an Adult Only Pool. A large gym with modern equipment is also available.  With a total of 3,960 rooms and suites spread in six towers, and a convention facility of more than 300,000 square feet, Caesars Palace is a luxury hotel and casino situated on the west side of the Las Vegas Strip between Bellagio and The Mirage in  Paradise, Nevada. The hotel has a large range of restaurants a casino with modern facilities and table games, a 4,500-square-foot 24-hour poker room, and many slot machines and video poker machines. It also has the main performance venue “The Colosseum” that seats 4,296 people and that contains a 22,450-square-foot stage.  Built on the site of the demolished Dunes hotel and casino on the Las Vegas Strip in Paradise, Nevada, Bellagio is a resort, luxury hotel, and casino mostly known for its 8-acre (3.2 ha) lake that houses the Fountains of Bellagio, a large dancing water fountain synchronized to music. The hotel features 3,933 rooms, a casino space, 5 outdoor swimming pools, and 4 spa tubs, in addition to a seasonal outdoor pool and other recreational amenities such as a fitness center. More than its iconic water show, there is the underwater story of “O” by Cirque du Soleil, fine dining restaurants, and a luxury shopping center.  The last, and the only hotel based out of the Las Vegas Strip, in our list top ten largest hotels in the United States of America (USA) is Hilton Hawaiian Village Waikiki Beach Resort, a veritable upscale village with five towers, 18 bars and restaurants, dozens of shops, five swimming pools, direct beach access, and a separate lagoon. Located in Waikiki Beach in Honolulu, Hawaii, Hilton Hawaiian Village Waikiki Beach Resort is the largest resort in the Western United States state with a total of 3,804 rooms. The resort first opened in 1955, and it has since grown to become the largest in the Hilton chain of hotels. 